race.comment: OBVIOUSLY ALBERT (9) strung together some good results, particularly at the mile, before a luckless effort at this track last start when he was caught on a limb for much of the race. Not a huge amount of depth to the form in this race so despite the fact he has won just once in 28 starts he looks the hardest to beat. SHE'S GOT TEETH (4) went very close two back at Taree then was looking for more ground last time out when a closing sixth over 1300m at this track. That run followed a 32-day let-up so she strips fitter and gets to her right trip now. RAINBOW BLESSING (5) capped off a consistent start to this campaign with a dominant maiden win over 1450m at Quirindi recently. Lightly raced filly who has plenty more to offer and should cope with this rise in class. OENOLOGY (1) has been hot and cold of late. Chance in this based on his run-on fifth, beaten 1.4 lengths, over 1509m at Port Macquarie two back. EJECT (3) goes well at the mile and will appreciate a return to firmer footing.
